## Applications

### Productivity

- [RescueTime](https://www.rescuetime.com/ref/31263) is a nice service that allows me to better understand my mobile and laptop usage. Overall I like to see where my time is going so that I have a better grasp of where I can make improvements.
- [Notion](https://www.notion.so/?r=6b8d609eb50943419db4d87c67fa558e) has been a great all-purpose tool that I've adopted. I use it through my day to record/perform many functions.
- [Evernote](https://www.evernote.com/referral/Registration.action?sig=8c3886860fefb20e7d080275664e98c0343346e37a1ce851d09c46de61a1a2de&uid=28190364) is used to hold all my scanned documents so that I can search through them using. I share this with my wife, so she is also able to pull up documents as needed.
- [TablePlus](https://tableplus.io/) is a GUI-based multi-purpose database management tool (i.e., MySQL, SQLite, PostgreSQL, etc...). I use to use a specific GUI application for the different databases, but this bundles them all into one clean GUI.
- [SourceTree](https://www.sourcetreeapp.com/) is my preferred GUI tool for working with `git` repositories. I personally do a lot of my work in the terminal, although I do like it for managing staging hunks of a file.
- [Dash](https://kapeli.com/dash) is a powerful programming documentation lookup tool. It has great integrations with Alfred as well.

### Utilities

- [Alfred](https://www.alfredapp.com/) is my replacement for Spotlight. It is customizable and powerful. I have the Powerpack which allows me to use workflows.
- [iStats Menu](https://bjango.com/mac/istatmenus/) provides me with finer-grain detail over my system with respect to CPU/Memory/Network/SSD/Battery.
- [Bartender](https://www.macbartender.com/) cleans up my menu bar on macOS so that I only have frequently used/looked applications up.
- [BetterSnapTool](https://itunes.apple.com/ca/app/bettersnaptool/id417375580) gives me the customizable keystrokes for moving my windows around on my desktop.
- [Monosnap](https://monosnap.com) is a great application for quickly sharing images, videos and GIFs. It also has expressive annotation tools built in.
- [1Password](https://1password.com/) has been an application that my wife and I have been using for a while. It excels at password management and secret concerns.

### Communication

- [Airmail](https://airmailapp.com/) is an email client that I have been using that offers a unified inbox and customizable swipe actions.
- [krisp](https://krisp.ai/) is a recent application I've been experimenting with as I've been doing much more remote conversations for work. It filters out background noises on the input/output audio channels.
- [Tweetbot](https://tapbots.com/tweetbot/mac/) is a native application for Twitter and keeps me up on recent tweets, the UI is also pretty good.
- [Slack](https://slack.com/) is the defacto communication tool for work.
- [Discord](https://discordapp.com/) is a great application that I use for persisted chatroom conversations with my family. I also use it for voice conversations when gaming.
- [Telegram](https://telegram.org/) is a communication application I use with a couple of friends.
- [Caprine](https://sindresorhus.com/caprine/) ([Facebook Messenger](https://www.messenger.com/)) is another communication tool that I use with family and friends.
